The box-sizing property controls how the total width and height of an element is calculated.

 Values of box-sizing:
Value	What It Means
content-box	Default: Width/height do not include padding or border.
border-box	Width/height include content + padding + border.

ðŸ§  Visual Example:
box-sizing: content-box; (default)
width: 200px;
padding: 20px;
ðŸ‘‰ Total width = 200 + 20 + 20 = 240px

box-sizing: border-box;
width: 200px;
padding: 20px;
ðŸ‘‰ Total width = 200px, including padding!

âœ… Best Practice:
Use this in your CSS:
* {
  box-sizing: border-box;
}
This makes layouts more predictable and easier to manage.

